.TH "vmw_validation_preload_res" 9 "vmw_validation_preload_res" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_validation_preload_res \- Preload the validation memory allocator for a call to vmw_validation_add_res().
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_validation_preload_res
.BI "(struct vmw_validation_context *ctx "  ","
.BI "unsigned int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
Pointer to the validation context.
.IP "size" 12
Size of the validation node extra data. See below.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Iff this function returns successfully, the next call to
\fBvmw_validation_add_res\fP with the same or smaller \fIsize\fP is guaranteed not to
sleep. An error is not fatal but voids the guarantee.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful, -EINVAL otherwise.
